author: BENOÎT FAUCON
title: IEA Sees Oil Market Remaining Oversupplied Next Year
text:
A top energy watchdog Tuesday warned that oil markets would likely remain oversupplied next year, as oil demand growth slows down amid an expected return of Iranian oil.
The assessment by the International Energy Agency--which represents some of the world’s largest oil consumers--is somewhat less upbeat than the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries which Monday said oil markets would start to rebalance themselves next...
